        desc: "The Tygart's remote Arden section is one of the most technical and undervisited Class III–IV runs in the Appalachians — a 10-mile gorge through Taylor County with no road access and dramatic sandstone walls. The upper river offers family-friendly floats through rolling farm country before the river drops into the gorge.",
