        desc: "The Sandy River drops from the glaciers of Mt. Hood to the Columbia, offering the closest whitewater to downtown Portland. The river\"s glacial-melt character means milky blue-green water in summer and crystal clarity in winter. The Sandy River Gorge provides a surprisingly wild Class II–III corridor just 30 minutes from the city. Marmot Dam was removed in 2007, restoring 100 miles of fish habitat.",
