        desc: "The only free-flowing non-tidal stretch of the Columbia River. The Hanford Reach runs 51 miles through the former Hanford nuclear reservation, where decades of restricted access accidentally preserved the last wild fall Chinook salmon run on the Columbia. The massive river flows past White Bluffs and through shrub-steppe desert in a setting unlike anything else in the Pacific Northwest.",
