        desc: "One of the most famous trout rivers in America. The Madison is a blue-ribbon trout stream flowing from Yellowstone National Park to Three Forks where it joins the Gallatin and Jefferson to form the Missouri. The 50-mile riffle between Quake and Ennis lakes is legendary — continuous riffled water holding wild rainbow and brown trout in extraordinary densities.",
