        g: '11319500', avg: 900, histFlow: 820, mx: 185, my: 100, abbr: 'CA',
        desc: "A Sierra Nevada gem flowing through the gold country of Amador and Calaveras counties. The Mokelumne offers excellent Class III–IV whitewater in a granite canyon setting, with the Electra Run being one of the most popular intermediate whitewater day trips in the central Sierra. Dam-controlled flows provide reliable summer paddling.",
        desig: 'National Wild & Scenic River (North Fork) · Eldorado National Forest',
