        desc: "The Napa River flows 55 miles through the heart of California wine country from Mount Saint Helena to San Pablo Bay. The upper river is a seasonal Class I riffle run through vineyards, while the lower tidal estuary offers year-round flatwater paddling past historic Napa and through restored wetlands. Fall paddling pairs perfectly with winery tours.",
