        g: '11365000', avg: 1100, histFlow: 1000, mx: 45, my: 152, abbr: 'CA',
        desc: "The Pit is northern California's longest river and one of its best kept trout fishing secrets — 207 miles from the Warner Mountains to Lake Shasta through a series of dam-controlled reaches known simply as 'Pit 3,' 'Pit 4,' 'Pit 5.' Wild rainbow trout average a foot-plus, and the volcanic canyon scenery below Lake Britton is some of the most dramatic in the state.",
