        desc: "The Palisades of the Kentucky River — 100 miles of 300-foot limestone cliffs through the heart of bourbon country. The Kentucky River flows 259 miles from the Appalachian foothills to the Ohio River, passing Camp Nelson, bourbon distilleries, and some of the most dramatic river gorge scenery in the eastern U.S. Class I water with stunning geology.",
