        desc: "The Chattooga River is the deep South's most legendary whitewater — a free-flowing National Wild & Scenic River forming the border between South Carolina and Georgia through the Sumter and Chattahoochee National Forests. Made famous by the 1972 film 'Deliverance,' the Chattooga delivers every level of whitewater from the committing Class IV–V of Section IV to the intermediate Class II–III of Section III.",
